claims:
1. A system for determining at least one characteristic of a transmitting coil generating a magnetic field, the system comprising:
a first measurement coil being wound in a first direction;
a second measurement coil being wound in a second direction;
the first measurement coil and the second measurement coil are adjacent to one another;
a voltage measuring device configured to measure a first voltage of the first measurement coil in response to the magnetic field generated by the transmitting coil and a second voltage of the second measurement coil in response to the magnetic field generated by the transmitting coil; and
at least one processor in communication with the voltage measuring device, the at least one processor being configured to determine the at least one characteristic of the transmitting coil based on a ratio between the first voltage and the second voltage at a predetermined frequency.
